http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Foreign-currency-seized-from-passenger/article14014714.ece

The Directorate of Revenue Intelligence (DRI) officials on Friday seized foreign currency - Euros and UAE Dirhams - valued nearly Rs.1.19 crore in Indian currency from a passenger at Rajiv Gandhi International Airport here. The passenger completed Immigration checking formalities and was about to board Sharjah-bound Air Arabia flight when the DRI officials checked his bagged.The foreign currency notes were concealed beneath the clothes, according to a press release.He was arrested and remanded in judicial custody.